reviewText:
There have been quite a few bundled sets of movies put on the market recently. Quite often, these packaged sets contain movies that rightfully failed at the box office. Sellers hope to make up in quantity what their bundles lack in quality.

However this packaged set of horror movies is different. It contains a preponderance of movies that would be individually worthwhile. This is one of the strongest sets of horror movies that I've seen, and one of the best values. I felt that at least six of the eight movies really offered something worth my time. Included here is:

"Mortuary" - Notable for some of its quirky characters;
"Ritual" - Some good on-screen presences, including the exotically beautiful Kristen Wilson;
"They" - Richly atmospheric and eerie throughout;

"Six Degrees of Helter Skelter" - A good trivia tour of the scenes of the Manson murders;
"The Hole" - An intelligent study of a girl who would do anything for love - including THAT;
"The Nameless" - a well-dubbed film about cultivating the ultimate evil.

For me, the two failures in this set were "Children of the Corn III," a mish-mash of plot and gore - and "The Crow: Wicked Prayed," a mish-mash of obscene violence.

But you're bound to find something to suit your scare tastes here. Just be aware there are no extras offered in this package. The movies are presented plain, without scene selection options, subtitles, or commentaries.
